    java.io.Serializable

    public class TwoSameGlobalVarDeclException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    Runtime Exception extension that allows the user to throw an Two Same Global Variables Declaration Exception. Thrown usually if two variables of the same type are declared with the same name.
    Author:
    Valentin Eggermont - valentin.eggermont@student.unamur.be, Thomas Vanhaeren - thomas.vanhaeren@student.unamur.be
